# A Person want to know the smallest N digit number, provided the number of digits. Write a program to check whether entered number is smallest N digit number or not

n = int(input("Enter number of digits: "))
num = int(input("Enter a number: "))

smallest = 10 ** (n - 1)

if num == smallest:
    print("It is the smallest", n, "digit number")
else:
    print("It is NOT the smallest", n, "digit number")

# OUTPUT 
'''
Enter number of digits: 3
Enter a number: 100
It is the smallest 3 digit number
'''
